Clyira API — Alembic Migration Guide
=====================================

## Setup (first time on existing Render DB)

The Render DB already has all tables from SQLAlchemy create_all(). Mark the
baseline migration as applied without running it:

    cd apps/api
    alembic stamp 001_baseline

## Common commands

    # Apply all pending migrations:
    alembic upgrade head

    # Roll back one migration:
    alembic downgrade -1

    # Show current migration state:
    alembic current

    # Generate a new migration from model changes:
    alembic revision --autogenerate -m "add xyz column"

    # Show migration history:
    alembic history --verbose

## Creating a new migration

1. Make your model changes in apps/api/app/models/
2. Run: alembic revision --autogenerate -m "describe the change"
3. Review the generated file in alembic/versions/
4. Apply: alembic upgrade head

## Notes

- Migrations run asynchronously (asyncpg driver) via asyncio.run()
- DATABASE_URL is read from settings (env var or .env file)
- The baseline migration is safe to run on a fresh DB — it creates all tables
- On an existing DB, use `alembic stamp 001_baseline` to skip it
